cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SE 

The paper deals with evaluating machine learning-based anomaly detection for DDoS attacks in a cloud environment. This involves aspects of computer security (cs.CR) and networking (cs.NI). The use of autoencoders as the machine learning model involves aspects of deep learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper also discusses the implications of their findings for applying autoencoder-based AD in production, which involves aspects of software engineering (cs.SE).
